151 int32_t MmwDemo_LVDSStreamInit (void)
152 {
153  CBUFF_InitCfg initCfg;
154  int32_t retVal = MINUS_ONE;
155  int32_t errCode;
156 
157  /*************************************************************************************
158  * Open the CBUFF Driver:
159  *************************************************************************************/
160  memset ((void *)&initCfg, 0, sizeof(CBUFF_InitCfg));
161 
162  /* Populate the configuration: */
163  initCfg.socHandle = gMmwDssMCB.socHandle;
164  initCfg.enableECC = 0U;
165  initCfg.crcEnable = 1U;
166  /* Up to 1 SW session + 1 HW session can be configured for each subframe. Therefore max session is 2. */
167  initCfg.maxSessions = 2U;
168  initCfg.enableDebugMode = false;
169  initCfg.interface = CBUFF_Interface_LVDS;
170  initCfg.outputDataFmt = CBUFF_OutputDataFmt_16bit;
171  initCfg.u.lvdsCfg.crcEnable = 0U;
172  initCfg.u.lvdsCfg.msbFirst = 1U;
173  /* Enable all lanes available on the platform*/
174  initCfg.u.lvdsCfg.lvdsLaneEnable = 0x3U;
175  initCfg.u.lvdsCfg.ddrClockMode = 1U;
176  initCfg.u.lvdsCfg.ddrClockModeMux = 1U;
177 
178  /* Initialize the CBUFF Driver: */
179  gMmwDssMCB.lvdsStream.cbuffHandle = CBUFF_init (&initCfg, &errCode);
180  if (gMmwDssMCB.lvdsStream.cbuffHandle == NULL)
181  {
182  /* Error: Unable to initialize the CBUFF Driver */
183  System_printf("Error: CBUFF_init failed with [Error=%d]\n", errCode);
184  goto exit;
185  }
186 
187  /* Initialize the HSI Header Module: */
188  if (HSIHeader_init (&initCfg, &errCode) < 0)
189  {
190  /* Error: Unable to initialize the HSI Header Module */
191  System_printf("Error: HSIHeader_init failed with [Error=%d]\n", errCode);
192  goto exit;
193  }
194 
195  /* Populate EDMA resources */
196  MmwDemo_LVDSStream_EDMAInit();
197 
198  retVal = 0;
199 
200 exit:
201  return retVal;
202 }

215 static void MmwDemo_LVDSStream_EDMAAllocateCBUFFChannel
216 (
217  CBUFF_EDMAInfo* ptrEDMAInfo,
218  CBUFF_EDMAChannelCfg* ptrEDMACfg
219 )
220 {
221  if(ptrEDMAInfo->dmaNum == 0)
222  {
223  ptrEDMACfg->chainChannelsId = MMW_LVDS_STREAM_CBUFF_EDMA_CH_0;
224  ptrEDMACfg->shadowLinkChannelsId = MMW_LVDS_STREAM_CBUFF_EDMA_SHADOW_CH_0;
225  }
226  else if(ptrEDMAInfo->dmaNum == 1)
227  {
228  ptrEDMACfg->chainChannelsId = MMW_LVDS_STREAM_CBUFF_EDMA_CH_1;
229  ptrEDMACfg->shadowLinkChannelsId = MMW_LVDS_STREAM_CBUFF_EDMA_SHADOW_CH_1;
230  }
231  else
232  {
233  /* Max of 2 CBUFF sessions can be configured*/
234  MmwDemo_dssAssert (0);
235  }
236 }

254 static int32_t MmwDemo_LVDSStream_EDMAAllocateCBUFFHwChannel
255 (
256  CBUFF_EDMAInfo* ptrEDMAInfo,
257  CBUFF_EDMAChannelCfg* ptrEDMACfg
258 )
259 {
260  int32_t retVal = MINUS_ONE;
261  MmwDemo_LVDSStream_MCB_t *streamMCBPtr = &gMmwDssMCB.lvdsStream;
262 
263  if(ptrEDMAInfo->isFirstEDMAChannel)
264  {
265  MmwDemo_LVDSStream_EDMAAllocateCBUFFChannel(ptrEDMAInfo, ptrEDMACfg);
266  retVal = 0;
267  }
268  else
269  {
270 
271  /* Sanity Check: Are there sufficient EDMA channels? */
272  if (streamMCBPtr->hwSessionEDMAChannelAllocatorIndex >= MMWDEMO_LVDS_STREAM_HW_SESSION_MAX_EDMA_CHANNEL)
273  {
274  /* Error: All the EDMA channels are allocated */
275  System_printf ("Error: MmwDemo_LVDSStream_EDMAAllocateCBUFFChannel failed. HW channel index=%d\n",
276  streamMCBPtr->hwSessionEDMAChannelAllocatorIndex);
277  goto exit;
278  }
279 
280  /* Copy over the allocated EDMA configuration. */
281  memcpy ((void *)ptrEDMACfg,
282  (void*)&streamMCBPtr->hwSessionEDMAChannelTable[streamMCBPtr->hwSessionEDMAChannelAllocatorIndex],
283  sizeof(CBUFF_EDMAChannelCfg));
284 
285  /* Increment the allocator index: */
286  streamMCBPtr->hwSessionEDMAChannelAllocatorIndex++;
287 
288  /* EDMA Channel allocated successfully */
289  retVal = 0;
290  }
291 
292 exit:
293  return retVal;
294 }

362 static void MmwDemo_LVDSStream_EDMAFreeCBUFFHwChannel (CBUFF_EDMAChannelCfg* ptrEDMACfg)
363 {
364  uint8_t index;
365  MmwDemo_LVDSStream_MCB_t *streamMCBPtr = &gMmwDssMCB.lvdsStream;
366 
367  if((ptrEDMACfg->chainChannelsId == MMW_LVDS_STREAM_CBUFF_EDMA_CH_0) ||
368  (ptrEDMACfg->chainChannelsId == MMW_LVDS_STREAM_CBUFF_EDMA_CH_1))
369  {
370  /*This is the CBUFF trigger channel. It is not part of the resource table so
371  nothing needs to be done*/
372  goto exit;
373  }
374 
375  for (index = 0U; index < MMWDEMO_LVDS_STREAM_HW_SESSION_MAX_EDMA_CHANNEL; index++)
376  {
377  /* Do we have a match? */
378  if (memcmp ((void*)ptrEDMACfg,
379  (void*)&streamMCBPtr->hwSessionEDMAChannelTable[index],
380  sizeof(CBUFF_EDMAChannelCfg)) == 0)
381  {
382  /* Yes: Decrement the HW Session index */
383  streamMCBPtr->hwSessionEDMAChannelAllocatorIndex--;
384  goto exit;
385  }
386  }
387 
388  /* Sanity Check: We should have had a match. An assertion is thrown to indicate that the EDMA channel
389  * being cleaned up does not belong to the table*/
390  MmwDemo_dssAssert (0);
391 
392 exit:
393  return;
394 }

452 void MmwDemo_LVDSStreamDeleteHwSession (CBUFF_SessionHandle sessionHandle)
453 {
454  int32_t errCode;
455  MmwDemo_LVDSStream_MCB_t* streamMcb = &gMmwDssMCB.lvdsStream;
456 
457  /* Delete session*/
458  if (CBUFF_deleteSession (sessionHandle, &errCode) < 0)
459  {
460  /* Error: Unable to delete the session. */
461  System_printf ("Error: MmwDemo_LVDSStreamDeleteHwSession CBUFF_deleteSession failed. Error code %d\n", errCode);
462  MmwDemo_dssAssert(0);
463  return;
464  }
465 
466  gMmwDssMCB.lvdsStream.hwSessionHandle = NULL;
467 
468  /* Did we stream out with the HSI Header? */
469  if (gMmwDssMCB.cliCfg[gMmwDssMCB.subFrameIndx].lvdsStreamCfg.isHeaderEnabled)
470  {
471  /* Delete the HSI Header: */
472  if (HSIHeader_deleteHeader (&streamMcb->hwSessionHSIHeader, &errCode) < 0)
473  {
474  /* Error: Unable to delete the HSI Header */
475  System_printf ("Error: MmwDemo_LVDSStreamDeleteHwSession HSIHeader_deleteHeader failed. Error code %d\n", errCode);
476  MmwDemo_dssAssert(0);
477  return;
478  }
479  }
480 }

536 static void MmwDemo_LVDSStream_HwTriggerFrameDone (CBUFF_SessionHandle sessionHandle)
537 {
538  int32_t errCode;
539 
540  /* Increment stats*/
541  gMmwDssMCB.lvdsStream.hwFrameDoneCount++;
542 
543  if(sessionHandle != NULL)
544  {
545  /* There are 2 cases to consider:
546  Only one subframe configured (legacy frame):
547  If there is a software session configured for this subframe, we need to
548  deactivate the HW session here.
549 
550  More than one subframe configured:
551  If there is more than one subframe we need to deactivate the HW
552  session here as other subframes may have configured a HW session.
553  In this case (more than one subframe), the HW session is always created
554  and activated in the MmwDemo_dssDataPathReconfig*/
555  if((gMmwDssMCB.numSubFrames > 1) ||
556  (gMmwDssMCB.dataPathObj[0].cliCfg->lvdsStreamCfg.isSwEnabled == 1))
557  {
558  if(CBUFF_deactivateSession (sessionHandle, &errCode) < 0)
559  {
560  /* Error: Unable to deactivate the session. */
561  DebugP_assert(0);
562  return;
563  }
564  }
565  }
566  else
567  {
568  DebugP_assert(0);
569  }
570 
571  return;
572 }
573 
586 static void MmwDemo_LVDSStream_SwTriggerFrameDone (CBUFF_SessionHandle sessionHandle)
587 {
588  int32_t errCode;
589 
590  /* Increment stats*/
591  gMmwDssMCB.lvdsStream.swFrameDoneCount++;
592 
593  if(sessionHandle != NULL)
594  {
595  if(CBUFF_deactivateSession (sessionHandle, &errCode) < 0)
596  {
597  /* Error: Unable to deactivate the session. */
598  DebugP_assert(0);
599  return;
600  }
601 
602  /*If only one subframe has been configured (legacy frame) and
603  a HW session has been configured for that subframe, we need to
604  enable it here as for the legacy frame the HW is NOT reconfigured
605  every frame.
606  If more than one subframe is configured, the HW
607  session is reconfigured and activated every subframe
608  in the datapath reconfigure function, not here.*/
609  if((gMmwDssMCB.numSubFrames == 1) &&
610  (gMmwDssMCB.lvdsStream.hwSessionHandle != NULL))
611  {
612  if(CBUFF_activateSession (gMmwDssMCB.lvdsStream.hwSessionHandle, &errCode) < 0)
613  {
614  DebugP_assert(0);
615  }
616  }
617  }
618  else
619  {
620  DebugP_assert(0);
621  }
622 
623  return;
624 }

637 int32_t MmwDemo_LVDSStreamHwConfig (MmwDemo_DSS_DataPathObj *datPathObj)
638 {
639  CBUFF_SessionCfg sessionCfg;
640  MmwDemo_LVDSStream_MCB_t* streamMcb = &gMmwDssMCB.lvdsStream;
641  int32_t errCode;
642  int32_t retVal = MINUS_ONE;
643 
644  memset ((void*)&sessionCfg, 0, sizeof(CBUFF_SessionCfg));
645 
646  /* Populate the configuration: */
647  sessionCfg.executionMode = CBUFF_SessionExecuteMode_HW;
648  sessionCfg.edmaHandle = gMmwDssMCB.dataPathContext.edmaHandle[MMW_LVDS_STREAM_EDMA_INSTANCE];
649  sessionCfg.allocateEDMAChannelFxn = MmwDemo_LVDSStream_EDMAAllocateCBUFFHwChannel;
650  sessionCfg.freeEDMAChannelFxn = MmwDemo_LVDSStream_EDMAFreeCBUFFHwChannel;
651  sessionCfg.frameDoneCallbackFxn = MmwDemo_LVDSStream_HwTriggerFrameDone;
652  sessionCfg.dataType = CBUFF_DataType_COMPLEX;
653  sessionCfg.u.hwCfg.dataMode = (CBUFF_DataMode)datPathObj->cliCfg->adcBufCfg.chInterleave;
654 
655  /* Populate the HW Session configuration: */
656  sessionCfg.u.hwCfg.adcBufHandle = gMmwDssMCB.dataPathContext.adcbufHandle;
657  sessionCfg.u.hwCfg.numADCSamples = datPathObj->numAdcSamples;
658  sessionCfg.u.hwCfg.numChirpsPerFrame = datPathObj->numChirpsPerFrame;
659  sessionCfg.u.hwCfg.chirpMode = datPathObj->numChirpsPerChirpEvent;
660  sessionCfg.u.hwCfg.opMode = CBUFF_OperationalMode_CHIRP;
661 
662  switch(datPathObj->cliCfg->lvdsStreamCfg.dataFmt)
663  {
664  case 1:
665  sessionCfg.u.hwCfg.dataFormat = CBUFF_DataFmt_ADC_DATA;
666  break;
667  case 2:
668  sessionCfg.u.hwCfg.dataFormat = CBUFF_DataFmt_CP_ADC;
669  break;
670  case 3:
671  sessionCfg.u.hwCfg.dataFormat = CBUFF_DataFmt_ADC_CP;
672  break;
673  case 4:
674  sessionCfg.u.hwCfg.dataFormat = CBUFF_DataFmt_CP_ADC_CQ;
675  sessionCfg.u.hwCfg.cqSize[0] = 0;
676  sessionCfg.u.hwCfg.cqSize[1] = HSIHeader_toCBUFFUnits(datPathObj->datapathCQ.sigImgMonTotalSize);
677  sessionCfg.u.hwCfg.cqSize[2] = HSIHeader_toCBUFFUnits(datPathObj->datapathCQ.satMonTotalSize);
678  break;
679  default:
680  System_printf ("Error: lvdsStreamCfg dataFmt %d is invalid\n", datPathObj->cliCfg->lvdsStreamCfg.dataFmt);
681  MmwDemo_dssAssert(0);
682  break;
683  }
684 
685  if(datPathObj->cliCfg->lvdsStreamCfg.isHeaderEnabled)
686  {
687  /* Create the HSI Header to be used for the HW Session: */
688  if (HSIHeader_createHeader (&sessionCfg, false, &(streamMcb->hwSessionHSIHeader), &errCode) < 0)
689  {
690  /* Error: Unable to create the HSI Header; report the error */
691  System_printf("Error: MmwDemo_LVDSStream_config unable to create HW HSI header with [Error=%d]\n", errCode);
692  goto exit;
693  }
694 
695  /* Setup the header in the CBUFF session configuration: */
696  sessionCfg.header.size = HSIHeader_getHeaderSize(&streamMcb->hwSessionHSIHeader);
697  sessionCfg.header.address = (uint32_t)&(streamMcb->hwSessionHSIHeader);
698  }
699 
700  /* Create the HW Session: */
701  streamMcb->hwSessionHandle = CBUFF_createSession (gMmwDssMCB.lvdsStream.cbuffHandle, &sessionCfg,&errCode);
702 
703  if (streamMcb->hwSessionHandle == NULL)
704  {
705  /* Error: Unable to create the CBUFF hardware session */
706  System_printf("Error: MmwDemo_LVDSStream_config unable to create the CBUFF hardware session with [Error=%d]\n", errCode);
707  goto exit;
708  }
709 
710  /* Control comes here implies that the LVDS Stream has been configured successfully */
711  retVal = 0;
712 
713 exit:
714  return retVal;
715 }
716 
728 int32_t MmwDemo_LVDSStreamSwConfig (MmwDemo_DSS_DataPathObj *datPathObj)
729 {
730  CBUFF_SessionCfg sessionCfg;
731  MmwDemo_LVDSStream_MCB_t* streamMcb = &gMmwDssMCB.lvdsStream;
732  int32_t errCode;
733  int32_t retVal = MINUS_ONE;
734 
735  memset ((void*)&sessionCfg, 0, sizeof(CBUFF_SessionCfg));
736 
737  /* Populate the configuration: */
738  sessionCfg.executionMode = CBUFF_SessionExecuteMode_SW;
739  sessionCfg.edmaHandle = gMmwDssMCB.dataPathContext.edmaHandle[MMW_LVDS_STREAM_EDMA_INSTANCE];
740  sessionCfg.allocateEDMAChannelFxn = MmwDemo_LVDSStream_EDMAAllocateCBUFFSwChannel;
741  sessionCfg.freeEDMAChannelFxn = MmwDemo_LVDSStream_EDMAFreeCBUFFSwChannel;
742  sessionCfg.frameDoneCallbackFxn = MmwDemo_LVDSStream_SwTriggerFrameDone;
743  sessionCfg.dataType = CBUFF_DataType_COMPLEX;
744  sessionCfg.u.swCfg.userBufferInfo[0].size = HSIHeader_toCBUFFUnits(sizeof(MmwDemo_LVDSUserDataHeader_t));
745  sessionCfg.u.swCfg.userBufferInfo[0].address = (uint32_t)&(streamMcb->userDataHeader);
746  if(datPathObj->numDetObj != 0)
747  {
748  sessionCfg.u.swCfg.userBufferInfo[1].size = HSIHeader_toCBUFFUnits((datPathObj->numDetObj) * sizeof(MmwDemo_detectedObj));
749  sessionCfg.u.swCfg.userBufferInfo[1].address = (uint32_t)datPathObj->detObj2D;
750  }
751  else
752  {
753  sessionCfg.u.swCfg.userBufferInfo[1].size = 0;
754  sessionCfg.u.swCfg.userBufferInfo[1].address = 0;
755  }
756 
757  /* Do we need to enable the header? */
758  if(datPathObj->cliCfg->lvdsStreamCfg.isHeaderEnabled)
759  {
760  /* Create the HSI Header to be used for the HW Session: */
761  if (HSIHeader_createHeader (&sessionCfg, true, &(streamMcb->swSessionHSIHeader), &errCode) < 0)
762  {
763  /* Error: Unable to create the HSI Header; report the error */
764  System_printf("Error: MmwDemo_LVDSStream_config unable to create HW HSI header with [Error=%d]\n", errCode);
765  goto exit;
766  }
767 
768  /* Setup the header in the CBUFF session configuration: */
769  sessionCfg.header.size = HSIHeader_getHeaderSize(&streamMcb->swSessionHSIHeader);
770  sessionCfg.header.address = (uint32_t)&(streamMcb->swSessionHSIHeader);
771  }
772 
773  /* Create the SW Session. */
774  streamMcb->swSessionHandle = CBUFF_createSession (gMmwDssMCB.lvdsStream.cbuffHandle, &sessionCfg, &errCode);
775 
776  if (streamMcb->swSessionHandle == NULL)
777  {
778  /* Error: Unable to create the CBUFF SW session */
779  System_printf("Error: MmwDemo_LVDSStream_config unable to create the CBUFF SW session with [Error=%d]\n", errCode);
780  goto exit;
781  }
782 
783  /* Control comes here implies that the LVDS Stream has been configured successfully */
784  retVal = 0;
785 
786 exit:
787  return retVal;
788 }
